FT  08 JUL 93 / People: Non-executive directors - Gresham Telecomputing
Hamish Donaldson, the former Hill Samuel chief executive who quit two years
ago after the bank made heavy losses, has been appointed a non-executive
director at Gresham Telecomputing, the USM-quoted software and computer
broking group. He is also a non-executive director at the Lines Partnership
and at London Bridge Finance, a former Hill Samuel subsidiary specialising
in credit insurance coverage.
